body_html:
arm64-v8a is a higher-performing 64-bit variant of the ARM architecture that only a subset of armeabi-v7a compatible devices support. If you add both to your apk your device will pick the highest compatible target available, but if you only add arm64-v8a and your device doesn't support it you may get error messages like the above.

You can see what .so libs are packaged in your apk with unzip -v tensorflow_demo.apk

body:
arm64-v8a is a higher-performing 64-bit variant of the ARM architecture that only a subset of armeabi-v7a compatible devices support. If you add both to your apk your device will pick the highest compatible target available, but if you only add arm64-v8a and your device doesn't support it you may get error messages like the above.

You can see what .so libs are packaged in your apk with `unzip -v tensorflow_demo.apk`
